instruction:
An `if` runs code when the condition is true. But what about when it is false?

That is what `else` is for. One or the other will always run — never both, never neither.

```
if score >= 50 {
    fmt.Println("Pass")
} else {
    fmt.Println("Fail")
}
```

Change `score` to 40 and run it. Then change it to 60 and run it again.

